    "body": "# Closing SaraFun\n\n> I closed a satellite restaurant after four months. Not because it lost money — because I opened it before I had the one person who runs a kitchen when I'm gone.\n\n## Hooks — write 5+, pick 1\n1. I closed a restaurant this year. Here's the part nobody posts.\n2. I shut one of my shops down in April. Best money I didn't keep spending.\n3. Everyone says don't quit. I quit a whole restaurant. On purpose.\n4. This shop was open four months. Then I killed it.\n5. The mistake wasn't opening it. It was opening it without one guy.\n\n**Chosen hook:** #2\n\n## Beat sheet\n\n| Beat | Time | Voiceover | On-screen / B-roll |\n|------|------|-----------|--------------------|\n| Hook | 0–3s | I shut one of my shops down in April. | Face, tight. Pinned text \"Closed a shop. On purpose.\" |\n| Context | 3–8s | Four months open. Then I closed it. | Throwback: shop day-1 photo, slow zoom |\n| Body A | 8–15s | Not because it lost money. Because I opened it before I had the one person who runs a kitchen when I'm not there. | B-roll: empty kitchen, keys on counter |\n| Re-hook | 15–17s | So every problem came straight to my phone. | Face snap, hold phone |\n| Body B | 17–28s | Supplier's late, my phone. Cook quits, my phone. I was running it from a different city, which, yeah, that's on me. | Phone notifications, WhatsApp, drive shots |\n| Re-hook 2 | 28–32s | The main shop was fine the whole time. | Face return, slower. Cut to main shop busy |\n| Payoff | 32–40s | Because that one has the guy. So I added it up. Closing was cheaper than keeping it on life support. | Proof shot: closure math / P&L, number circled |\n| Close | 40–45s | Two cooks from the closed one moved to the main kitchen. They start Monday. | Cooks at the line, prepping |\n\n## Voiceover — clean read\n\nI shut one of my shops down in April. Four months open. Then I closed it. Not because it lost money. Because I opened it before I had the one person who runs a kitchen when I'm not there. So every problem came straight to my phone. Supplier's late, my phone. Cook quits, my phone. I was running it from a different city, which, yeah, that's on me. The main shop was fine the whole time, because that one has the guy. So I added it up. Closing was cheaper than keeping it on life support. Two cooks from the closed one moved to the main kitchen. They start Monday.\n\n## On-screen text\n- **Pinned (top):** Closed a shop. On purpose.\n- **Key captions / numbers (these carry the rupiah — never spoken):** closure math / final P&L screenshot with the cost-of-staying number circled. Real timestamp visible.\n\n## B-roll shot list\n- [ ] Day-1 throwback photo of SaraFun (camera roll, date stamp)\n- [ ] Empty kitchen, keys on the counter\n- [ ] Phone buzzing — WhatsApp / supplier messages\n- [ ] Drive / different-city shot (windshield)\n- [ ] Main shop during service (the contrast)\n- [ ] Two cooks prepping at the main line\n\n## Proof shot\n- **Number on screen:** monthly cost of keeping SaraFun open vs. one-time close cost\n- **Lands on this line:** \"Closing was cheaper than keeping it on life support.\"\n\n## Post caption + hashtags\n\nClosed SaraFun in April. Four months in. The shop wasn't the mistake — opening it before the kitchen could run without me was. Two of the cooks start at the main shop Monday.\n\n#smallbusiness #restaurant #buildinpublic #operator #foundersjourney\n\n## Notes\n- **Pronunciation flags:** \"satellite\" (avoid — say \"the second shop\"). \"P&L\" stays on screen, not spoken.\n- **Music / SFX:** low, no drop. Phone-buzz SFX on the \"my phone\" repeats."
