    "body": "# The ticket rail is my Stripe dashboard\n\n> Translating restaurant ops into builder language: the kitchen ticket rail is a real-time throughput dashboard, the 7pm queue is a hockey stick.\n\n## Hooks — write 5+, pick 1\n1. You ship code. I ship 1,200 plates a day. Same loop.\n2. This is my production dashboard. It's a metal rail with paper on it.\n3. Builders watch Stripe. I watch this rail at 7pm.\n4. Everyone's got a dashboard. Mine prints tickets and catches fire.\n5. I run a kitchen like a server. Here's the part that maps one-to-one.\n\n**Chosen hook:** #1\n\n## Beat sheet\n\n| Beat | Time | Voiceover | On-screen / B-roll |\n|------|------|-----------|--------------------|\n| Hook | 0–3s | You ship code. I ship 1,200 plates a day. | Open on the ticket rail, tickets flying |\n| Context | 3–8s | Same loop. Measure, fix, ship. Just hotter. | Wok firing, line moving |\n| Body A | 8–15s | This rail is my throughput graph. Tickets pile up, that's my queue going red. | Close on the rail filling up |\n| Re-hook | 15–17s | And the 7pm rush is the hockey stick everyone wants. | Face snap |\n| Body B | 17–28s | Except I can't A/B test a Saturday. If prep's wrong at 5, the whole night's slow. So the fix has to happen before service, not during. | Prep shots, 5pm clock, staff briefing |\n| Re-hook 2 | 28–32s | Same as a deploy. You don't fix it live. | Face return |\n| Payoff | 32–40s | So I built the prep checklist into the POS. Now the kitchen sees the night's plan before I show up. | Proof shot: POS prep screen, orders count |\n| Close | 40–45s | Tonight it's 1,200 plates and one new cook. We'll see. | Cook plating, rail in background |\n\n## Voiceover — clean read\n\nYou ship code. I ship 1,200 plates a day. Same loop. Measure, fix, ship. Just hotter. This rail is my throughput graph. Tickets pile up, that's my queue going red. And the 7pm rush is the hockey stick everyone wants. Except I can't A/B test a Saturday. If prep's wrong at 5, the whole night's slow. So the fix has to happen before service, not during. Same as a deploy. You don't fix it live. So I built the prep checklist into the POS. Now the kitchen sees the night's plan before I show up. Tonight it's 1,200 plates and one new cook. We'll see.\n\n## On-screen text\n- **Pinned (top):** My production dashboard.\n- **Key captions / numbers:** \"1,200 plates / day\" count-up chip. POS daily orders on the proof shot (counts only — fine to show).\n\n## B-roll shot list\n- [ ] Ticket rail filling during rush (the hero shot)\n- [ ] Wok firing, flame\n- [ ] 5pm clock + prep in progress\n- [ ] Staff briefing, headcount pan\n- [ ] POS prep checklist screen\n- [ ] New cook plating\n\n## Proof shot\n- **Number on screen:** POS daily orders / plates count (a count, not rupiah)\n- **Lands on this line:** \"Now the kitchen sees the night's plan before I show up.\"\n\n## Post caption + hashtags\n\nThe ticket rail is the most honest dashboard I own. Built the prep checklist into our POS so the night's plan lands before service starts. Same loop as shipping software, just hotter.\n\n#restaurant #ops #buildinpublic #foodbusiness #operator\n\n## Notes\n- **Pronunciation flags:** \"throughput\" (one hard word — say it slow, once). Avoid \"A/B test\" stumble; rehearse.\n- **Music / SFX:** kitchen ambience under VO, ticket-print SFX on rail shots."
