    "body": "# The one-bottleneck rule\n\n> Most custom software fails because it tries to digitize everything. I only build for the single bottleneck that's actually costing the business right now.\n\n## Hooks — write 5+, pick 1\n1. I never build the whole system. I find the one thing that's on fire.\n2. Most custom software fails for the same reason. It does too much.\n3. Clients want ten features. I usually ship one.\n4. The first thing I do isn't code. It's figure out what to ignore.\n5. You don't need a system. You need one screen that fixes one problem.\n\n**Chosen hook:** TBD\n\n## Beat sheet\n\n| Beat | Time | Voiceover | On-screen / B-roll |\n|------|------|-----------|--------------------|\n| Hook | 0–3s | I never build the whole system. I find the one thing that's on fire. | Whiteboard, circling one box |\n| Body A | 3–14s | Most custom software dies because it tries to digitize everything. Booking, stock, payroll, all at once. Too much. So nobody uses it. | Whiteboard: many boxes, then one circled |\n| Re-hook | 14–18s | So I do the opposite. | Face snap |\n| Body B | 18–26s | I sit with the operator and find the one thing that wakes them up at 3am. Then I build only that. One screen. One problem. | Screen-record: single clean screen |\n| Close | 26–30s | The rest can stay a spreadsheet. Honestly, it usually does. | Spreadsheet on screen, shrug-energy cut |\n\n## Voiceover — clean read\n\nI never build the whole system. I find the one thing that's on fire. Most custom software dies because it tries to digitize everything. Booking, stock, payroll, all at once. Too much. So nobody uses it. So I do the opposite. I sit with the operator and find the one thing that wakes them up at 3am. Then I build only that. One screen. One problem. The rest can stay a spreadsheet. Honestly, it usually does.\n\n## On-screen text\n- **Pinned (top):** Build one thing. Ignore the rest.\n- **Key captions / numbers:** highlight \"one screen, one problem.\"\n\n## B-roll shot list\n- [ ] Whiteboard: many boxes drawn, one circled live\n- [ ] Screen-record of a single clean screen\n- [ ] Spreadsheet still in use (the honest part)\n\n## Proof shot\n- **Number on screen:** optional — none needed for a 30s take\n- **Lands on this line:** n/a\n\n## Post caption + hashtags\n\nCustom software usually fails because it tries to do everything. I build for the one bottleneck that's costing the business right now, and let the rest stay a spreadsheet.\n\n#automation #buildinpublic #softwaredevelopment #systems #smallbusiness\n\n## Notes\n- **Pronunciation flags:** \"digitize\" (rehearse). \"payroll\" crisp.\n- **Music / SFX:** minimal. This one's idea-stage — refine hook before shooting."
